        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head id="a5" altrender="organizational history">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
            <p>The United Mineworkers of America (UMWA) was founded in Columbus, Ohio in 1890. In
                1967, W.A. "Tony" Boyle was the President of the UMWA.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
            <p>This collection consists of reports, speeches, and audiorecordings from the United
                Mineworkers of America convention, 1976.</p>
        </scopecontent>
